Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2}(cloves) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @cherry tomatoes{125%g}. Halve the @lemon{1/2}.

Roughly chop the @parsley{5%g}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all).

Pop the peppers onto a lined #baking tray{} and drizzle with @oil{to taste}.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} and toss to coat.

Roast in your oven until charred and soft, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Halfway through cooking, add the tomatoes to the tray and pop back into the
oven for the remaining time.

Once cooked, remove from your oven and cover with #foil{} to keep warm.

While the veg roasts, place a large pan over high heat with a drizzle of
@oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the @diced Irish chicken breast{260%g} and @chorizo{100%g}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Season well with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Fry until browned, ~{4-6%minutes}. Stir occasionally to avoid sticking.

> TIP: You may want to do this in batches to avoid stewing the chicken.

Stir the garlic and @paprika{1%sachet} into the pan and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @rice{150%g}.

Stir well to fully coat and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Pour in @water{to taste} along with the @chicken stock{1%sachet}.

Bring the #pan{} to the boil.

Reduce the heat to medium, cover with a #lid{} (or some foil) and cook for
~{10%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove from the heat and set aside (still covered) for another
~{10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once ready, add in the roasted pepper and tomato along with a squeeze of
@lemon juice{from 1/2 lemon} and half the parsley.

Stir everything to combine, then taste and season with @salt{to taste},
@pepper{to taste} and more lemon juice if you like.

Cut any remaining lemon into wedges.

Sprinkle on the remaining parsley.

Place the pan on the table, top with lemon wedges, and let everyone help
themselves.